===== Program =====

It is important to have installed beforehand in your laptops the VO-tools to be used in the School, namely:

     * [[http://aladin.u-strasbg.fr/java/download/Aladin.jar|ALADIN]] (Download the Aladin.jar file and execute it from a terminal using "**java -Xmx2048m -jar Aladin.jar**"). Official version: v10 
     * [[http://www.star.bris.ac.uk/~mbt/topcat/topcat-full.jar|TOPCAT]] (Download the topcat-full.jar file and execute it from a terminal using "**java -jar topcat-full.jar**"). Official version: v4.6-2
       * See detailed instructions under http://www.star.bris.ac.uk/~mbt/topcat/ 
     * [[http://www.star.bris.ac.uk/~mbt/stilts/stilts.jar|STILTS]] (Download the stilts.jar file and execute it from a terminal using "**java -jar stilts.jar**"). Official version: v3.1-5 
       * See detailed instructions under http://www.star.bris.ac.uk/~mbt/stilts/
     * [[http://svo2.cab.inta-csic.es/theory/vosa/|VOSA]] (Web server. You don't need to install anything). Official version: v6.0

     * Java 1.8 or a later version has to be installed on your system. 
       * To check the Java installation from a terminal, type the command line: java -version
       * You can download the latest JRE version from: https://www.java.com/en/download/


